Sprint 18 - Top teachers leaderboard (6.4) + transcript broadcast (4.3 complete)

6.4 Top teachers (Data Moat):
- SUPABASE_TOP_TEACHERS.sql: profiles.public_teacher opt-in flag,
  public_top_teachers(p_limit) SECURITY DEFINER RPC aggregating
  events_held / total_players / total_points / avg_points only for
  teachers with public_teacher=TRUE AND at least one event flagged
  is_public_scoreboard=TRUE. Privacy-first.
- /scoreboard now has tab toggle: Top players <-> Top teachers,
  with rank badges, indigo gradient on top-3.
- New ProfileTab.jsx in Dashboard sidebar (User icon) — display
  name + "Public teacher" toggle, default OFF.

4.3 Live transcription broadcast (foundation -> complete):
- LiveCaptions extended with broadcastChannel prop; lazily
  subscribes to Supabase Realtime channel `captions:CODE` while
  enabled and emits {text, ts, lang} on each final transcript.
- Presenter passes eventCode -> broadcast.
- New ParticipantCaptions.jsx mounted on Participant view: own
  toggle (bottom-right CC button, persist localStorage), WCAG AA
  bottom bar with last 5 captions, default OFF (data/battery).
- Zero DB schema (broadcast channels are ephemeral).

Build: green. New chunks - PublicScoreboard 2.95KB gz (was 2.71),
Dashboard 25.19KB gz (was ~24.7), EventWrapper 19.65KB gz.

Roadmap: 30/30 P0+P1 items complete; remaining 6.1/6.2/6.3 are
data-flywheel work that needs production usage to bootstrap.
